Male 32 here.
I recently went to an event where there was a higher-than-average probability that I might run into my ex girlfriend. She didn't end up being there, but the sole reminder of her existence was enough to shake me to my core and make me realise how little I actually feel for my current gf of more than 3 years. I feel like I'm the worst piece of shit on the planet. I might be wasting this girls' best years since I'm not sure at all if I want a future with her. She's been giving me clear signs for months now that she wants to get married and start a family sooner rather than later.

My ex was my first everything. I felt an otherworldly sort of happiness back then, I remember it indistinctly. I would have given everything to grow old with her. She was (and still is, sadly), by far, the prettiest, sexiest, cutest girl in the universe to me. I see random chicks on the street that kinda, remotely look like her, and I feel more lust than I do during sex with my current girlfriend, who looks vastly different than my first.

The breakup back then, again: more than 5 years ago at this point, was one of multiple factors that lead me to deciding that I don't want to even prioritise "happiness" in my life. I promised myself that I'd rather try to live a decent, commendable, kind life, focussing on improving circumstances for myself, my family and my close friends through hard work and dedication. In all honestly, I've been experiencing constant, solid amounts of happiness as a sort of side effect of that lifestyle, so I won't complain. But yeah, being reminded of that kind of "butterflies in stomach", pure bliss sort of happiness I felt with that girl back then, is eating me up inside.

The relationship with my first gf ended after just a few short months. She told me she didn't have enough feelings for me and continuing the relationship would be dishonest. I decided to not be a pathetic dog chasing after her and immediately just said "okay, then let's end this now." Never talked to her ever since. But, more or less secretly, my deepest, sole and most desired wish I ever had for all those years, was that famous second chance.

And now I have this situation with my current girlfriend. There's nothing wrong with her, but I honestly fear that the main two reasons I'm sticking with her, are
1) my commitment to doing what's decent and right. She keeps telling me how every day with me just keeps getting better and better, how she could not even picture her life without me for a single day and that she's blissfully happy every second she spends with me
2) the usual fear of staying alone / not being in time to start a family myself
I know I'm a disgusting, horrible piece of shit, just for that. I'm being dishonest, at the very least and this is kind of the worst kind of dishonesty I can imagine.

The only redeeming fact I can think of is that I'm 100% sure I won't ever be able to have as many feelings for any girl in the world as I did for my first girlfriend.
So even if I pulled through with what I am now afraid would be the mercilessly honest thing to do, breaking up with my current girlfriend, I'd still be trapped in endless emptiness. I don't know what to do. Just had to vent, I suppose.
